Commentary: Ishant comes around the wicket and bowls it on the pads with the angle. No swing first up just the ball going with the angle. Shadman glances it to square leg.
A slight bit of away movement on this one. Good length ball outside off, Ishant makes the ball curve away a bit. Shadman does not disturb that.
Length ball closer to the off pole, Shadman defends it to point.
Ishant goes full on middle and off, Shadman defends it with a straight bat. Not a lot of movement for Ishant so far.
Back of a length ball around the pads, Shadman tucks it to the on side.
Full outside off, Shadman leaves it alone. There is a bit of away swing on this one but that comes once the ball is past the stumps. Maiden to begin with.
Umesh comes over the wicket and bowls a full ball on off. Imrul starts his innings with a solid front foot defense. Hint of inward swing for Umesh.
Bangladesh up and running. On the pads, Kayes glances it to fine leg and gets off the mark. First run for Bangladesh with the pink ball.
Umesh is generating the swing here unlike his partner. Full and it comes in to the southpaw. Shadman defends it off the front foot.
Shadman gets underway as well. On the pads, Islam flicks it to fine leg and gets to the other end.
Fuller outside off, Kayes lets it carry to the keeper.
Full on off, Imrul defends it to the on side to get through the over. 2 off Umesh's first but the swing he generated will excite him.
Hint of away movement for Ishant. Good length ball outside off, Shadman initially looks to defend but then leaves it alone. Ishant a tad shorter than his usual lengths.

Beautiful! Ishant shows the seam and hits the deck hard around off, Shadman looks to defend but gets squared up as the ball moves away at the last moment. It was not far away from the edge and the off pole.
Length ball on off, Shadman nudges it to cover-point and gets a single.
This one comes in. Good length ball on off, Kayes looks to defend but does so off the outer half of his bat towards gully.
On the pads, Imrul glances it through square leg and gets a couple as Mayank Agarwal cleans it up with a slide.
Good amount of swing on this one. Outside off and swinging away. Kayes leaves it alone. Saha moves to his right and gathers the ball.
Good length ball outside off, Shadman shoulders arms to this one.
Full delivery down the leg side, Shadman looks to flick it but the ball glances his pad and goes to the keeper.
FOUR! Poor ball this from Umesh Yadav! Bowls it on a length way outside off, Shadman Islam stands tall and hammers the ball away through covers for the first boundary of the game.
On a length on middle, Islam works it to square leg.
FOUR! Thrashed! Umesh Yadav bowls a shorter delivery around off, Islam camps on his back foot and pulls it with disdain over the mid-wicket fielder for the second boundary of the over.
Full delivery outside off, Islam shoulders arms to this one.
On the fourth stump line, Imrul looks to play but then leaves it alone.
This one comes with the angle on off and middle. Kayes glances it using the angle through square leg for one.
Ishant makes this one come back in to the southpaw. Shadman hops on his crease and blocks it to the off side.
Outside off, Islam leaves it alone.
Way outside off, Shadman leaves it in a similar way to Steven Smith.
Another one outside off, Ishant wants Shadman to drive but Islam is not interested.
Good length ball on off, Kayes blocks it to point.
On a length on middle, Imrul works it to the leg side.
LEG BYE! Umesh Yadav bowls a good length ball on the pads, Kayes looks to flick it but the ball hits the pads and goes towards square leg. The batters steal a leg bye.
On a length outside off, Islam does not fiddle with it and allows the ball to go to the keeper.
Islam, yet again, lets this good length ball outside off go to the keeper.
Good length delivery on off, Islam attempts to defend it but it hits the outside half of the bat and rolls towards point.

NOT OUT! It has indeed come off his thigh pad. Kayes straightaway reviewed it indicating that the ball had come off his thigh pad and that is indeed the case. Back of a length around off, the ball jags away at the end. Kayes looks to defend but it goes off something behind to the keeper. The Indian players appeal and the umpire raises his finger after a brief thought. Kayes signals the 'T' straightaway. Replay rolls in and Ultra Edge shows no spike as it goes past the bat. The on-field decision is overturned and Kayes survives.
Outside off, Kayes leaves it alone. This one swings leaps and bounds.

OUT! LBW! India have their first wicket with the pink ball. It looked to be hitting the stumps and it is indeed hitting the leg stump. Slightly fuller on around off, Kayes gets across and looks to flick but misses. The ball hits his front pad and the Indian players go up in a confident appeal. The umpire agrees with them and raises his finger. Kayes has a word with his partner and reviews it. Replay rolls in. Ultra Edge first comes in and confirms no involvement of bat. Ball Tracker then comes in and it shows that the ball was going to hit the leg pole. Bangladesh lose their review. Kayes does not survive for long. The fans are up in joy and so are the players.
Bouncer to welcome the Bangladesh skipper. Mominul sways away from it.
Outside off, Haque leaves it alone.
Back of a length ball on off, Mominul hops and keeps it down. End of a very successful over from Ishant. Wicket maiden.

Almost gets a wicket off the first ball Shami bowls! Bowls it a shorter outside off, Shadman looks to leave the ball alone. It goes off the bottom half of the bat uppishly. Shami hares towards it to take the catch but it bounces way short. Lucky break for Shadman Islam.

NOT OUT! Waste of a review from India! How come Saha did not pick this one up? Shami bowls a good length ball swinging in. Shadman looks to defend it but the sneaks past the bat and pad going to Wriddhiman Saha who dives to his right to take the catch. The Indians appeal but the umpire shakes his head. Shami and Saha look confident and convince Kohli to go for the review. The Ultra Edge rolls in and it shows that there is clearly no bat on it. The ball has gone off the thigh pad and into the keeper's gloves. Both teams lose a review very early on in the game. What a start to the spell from the local lad, Mohammed Shami.
Short ball around the body, Shadman pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Back of a length ball outside off, Mominul leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Mominul defends it onto the ground. It hits him on his body off the surface and goes to the off side.
On the body, Mominul tucks it to the on side. Exciting over from Shami first up.
Length ball outside off, away swing on this one. Shadman has no interest in playing that.
Good keeping this from the local boy. Good length ball outside off, Shadman leaves it alone. The ball moves a lot after the stumps and Saha does really well to take it with a dive to his left.
Closer to the off pole but still outside. Shadman shoulders arms to this once again Smith style.
Jags this one back in. On middle and off, Islam defends it well.
Fuller outside off, Shadman does not play at it.
Back of a length on off, Shadman defends it with soft hands to the off side and takes a quick single to keep the strike.
Outside off and swinging away. Shadman shoulders arms to it. Once again there is swing once the ball is past the stumps.
Goes wide of the crease and bowls it on the fourth stump line. Shadman leaves it alone.

Length ball on off, Shadman defends it towards point. Mominul was looking to steal a single but Shadman says no. Umesh Yadav has a shy at the bowler's end but misses. Even if Umesh had hit Mominul would have been in. Good call from Shadman as the single was not there at all.
Back of a length around off, Islam defends it off his back foot.

WOW! This one has moved a long long way. Excellent take from Saha. Saha has found the toughest so far with this pink ball. Shami goes wide of the crease and makes it jag back in. The ball keeps coming in and it keeps going away from the wicketkeeper. as it goes to Saha. He dives to his right and saves a certain FOUR BYES.
Outside off, Islam leaves it alone.

OUT! Caught! Rohit Sharma has taken a stunner here! Good length ball around off, it shapes away at the last moment. It is in the channel of uncertainty. Mominul looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge. It goes between first and second slip. Rohit Sharma at second slip dives to his right and takes a superb one-handed catch. Had he not dived, one would feel it would have gone straight to Kohli but as they say if you feel like it is your catch at slip then you should go for it. That is exactly what Rohit has done here. The Bangladesh skipper departs for a duck.
Fuller on off, Mithun starts his innings with a front foot defense.

OUT! BOWLED! Umesh strikes again. Wicket, dot, wicket. This has been a brilliant over. Umesh fires one full ball which comes back in. Mithun looks to defend but gets a slight inside edge which takes the leg stump out for a toss. The crowd is up in joy and Bangladesh in deep, deep trouble here.
Length ball on off, Rahim plays it to point to start his innings.
On the pads, Mushfiqur flicks it to the on side.
On the fourth stump line, Rahim does not disturb that one. End of a magnificent over from Umesh.
Bouncer. It is outside the stumps, Islam looks to pull but then leaves it.
EDGED AND FOUR! Length ball on off, Shadman looks to drive but the ball moves away taking the outside edge of the bat and it goes over the man at third slip for a boundary.
FOUR! This time looked a bit more controlled. Good length ball around off, Shadman looks to run it down to third man but the ball takes the outside edge and goes wide of gully for a boundary.
On the pads, Islam glances it to the on side for a single.

OUT! Chopped on! Bangladesh's crisis man is out of here and the misery piles on. Back of a length ball on off, Mushfiqur looks to defend but he is a bit late on it. The ball takes the upper half of his bat and goes onto hit the stumps. A similar way in which Mushfiqur got out in the first Test. India did not look too good with the ball to start off with but now they are looking at their lethal best!
Shami fires another pacy ball. It is down the leg side though. Mahmudullah looks to flick but misses. End of a brilliant Shami over.
Full delivery on off, Shadman plays it back to the bowler.
On a length outside off, Shadman guides it to covers and takes a couple before the fielder from third man can clean it up.
FOUR! Strays down the leg side does Umesh Yadav! It is bowled on a length, which is picked off easily by Shadman Islam and goes into the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Short delivery on off, Shadmap pulls it towards deep square leg and takes a single.

EDGED BUT FALLS WELL SHORT! Good length ball outside off, Mahmudullah attempts to defend it but it goes off the outside edge towards Saha who collects it on the bounce diving forward. Played it with soft hands and that's probably why it did not carry to Wriddhiman Saha.
Good length delivery outside off, Mahmudullah lets the ball go to the keeper.
On the fourth stump line, Shadman leaves it alone.
Length ball way outside off. Shadman looks to cut but it comes off the lower half of his bat. It goes to the left of point. Jadeja there moves there swiftly and keeps it to a dot.
Good length ball on middle and off, Shadman looks to defend but it goes to the leg side off the inner half of his bat for a single.

FOUR BYES! This one does too much. Good length ball down the leg side, the ball keeps going away to the left of Saha. He dives but has no chance of saving that and the ball goes to the fine leg fence.
Good length ball outside off, Mahmudullah leaves it alone.
Shami wants Mahmudullah to drive but Mahmudullah is not tempted to and leaves it alone.
Full and wide outside off, Shadman looks to drive but misses.

OUT! Caught! Beautiful delivery from Umesh. Hardly anything Shadman could do. Bangladesh have half their side back in the hut now. Good length ball around off, Shadman is in two minds whether to play at it or not. He decides to have a poke at it. The ball shapes away and tickles the outside edge. It goes straight to Saha. He will not drop those even in his sleep. Half the side back in the pavilion. 100th Test dismissal for Wriddhiman Saha. Join quickest for India to achieve this feat for India along with Dhoni. One of the easiest ones to get to this landmark.
FOUR! Liton is off the mark in style. Slightly overpitched on the pads, Liton picks it early and flicks it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Now calmly leaves the length ball outside off.
FOUR! Poor ball and rightfully punished. Liton looks to be in the mood here. Length ball well outside off, Das slams it through backward point for a boundary.
Single to end the over. On the pads, LD looks to glance it to the leg side but it goes off his pad and they take a leg bye.
Fuller on the pads, Das works it to the leg side.
On off, Das defends it off the front foot.
Full and coming in. Das gets on his front foot and does well to defend it.
Length ball outside off, Das nudges it to point for one.
Outside off, Mahmudullah leaves it alone.

Good length ball around off, it comes back in. Mahmudullah looks to defend but it goes off his thigh pad. There is a stifled appeal but the umpire is not interested. The umpire waits and then signals it as run. Hawk Eye later on rolls in and it shows that the bat was not involved. It also shows that it was going over the stumps.
BEATEN! Beautiful bowling from Umesh Yadav! Good length ball outside off swinging away, Mahmudullah looks to defend it but passes the outside edge of the bat to the keeper.
FOUR! Poor ball from Yadav! He tends to stray down sometimes. Bowls it on the pads, Mahmudullah flicks it to fine leg and picks up an easy boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Mahmudullah shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, left alone.
Fullish delivery outside off, Mahmudullah blocks it to cover and looks for a single but is sent back by Das. Good decision as the single was not there.
BOUNCER! Umesh bowls this on off, Mahmudullah who does well to duck under it.
Starts with a full delivery on middle, Das pushes it back to Ishant.
Full delivery outside off, Das lunges forward and pushes it to point for a couple. Shubman Gill runs after it and cleans it up.
Full delivery on off, Liton drives this beautifully but finds the fielder at cover who dives to his right to stop the ball.
Fullish ball outside the off stump, Das shoulders arms to this one.
This time bowls it on a length outside off, Das has no problems in leaving this one alone.
Full delivery in the channel outside off, Liton once more does not fiddle with it.
Jadeja starts with a flighted ball on middle, Mahmudullah plays it back to the bowler.
Floated ball outside off, Mahmudullah pushes it to covers and wants a single but Das is not interested.
Tossed up ball on middle and leg, Mahmudullah flicks it to the leg side and takes a single.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Low full toss on middle and leg, Liton flicks it to deep mid-wicket and picks up his third boundary of the innings.
Flatter delivery outside off, Das plays it to cover off the back foot.
Fullish delivery on middle, Das works it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Mahmudullah shoulders arms and lets it go to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Mahmudullah blocks it back to Ishant.
Full delivery around off, Mahmudullah pushes it to cover-point for nothing.

OUT! CAUGHT! First it was Rohit Sharma who took a blinder, now it is Saha who takes what we can call a superhero catch. Brilliant stuff from the Indian keeper. Ishant Sharma bowls it on a length around off, the ball swings a bit late. Mahmudullah looks to defend it but the ball takes the outside edge and goes towards first slip. Saha, the local lad, dives to his right and takes a stunning catch inches above the ground with just one hand. Bangladesh lose their sixth wicket and slip further and further.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Nayeem looks to flick it away but it goes off his thigh pad towards square leg.

FOUR BYES! Beautiful bowling from Ishant Sharma! Good length ball swinging into the batsman. Nayeem looks to fend it but the ball cuts him in half, and goes right between the bat and pad. Saha dives to his left to collect it but fails to do so. The ball rolls to the fine leg fence.
Good length ball on off, Das defends it to point.

OUCH! That surely has hurt Das! Short ball on middle, Das looks to play the hook shot but the ball goes and hits his helmet. The ball rolls to point. Mohammed Shami and the rest enquire whether he is fine to continue. The physio is being called for the mandatory concussion check.
FOUR! This is how you reply after being hit on the grill. Short ball on off, Liton rocks on his back foot and pulls it with full authority to square leg for a boundary.
Full delivery outside off, Das lets the ball go to the keeper.
On a length on middle, Das looks to defend it but it goes off the inside half of the bat towards square leg. The batters cross for a single.

FOUR! Beautiful shot from Liton Das! He is looking in terrific touch out there. Ishant bowls a half-volley outside off, Das lunges forward and creams the drive to deep extra cover for another boundary.
Full delivery outside off, Das does not fiddle with it and lets the ball go to Saha.
Another full delivery outside off, Das lets the ball go to the keeper.
Ishant bowls a length delivery outside off, Das lets the ball pass through to the keeper.
Bowls a full delivery outside off, Ebadot does not fiddle with it and leaves it well alone.
BEATEN! Beautiful ball from Ishant! Good lenght ball outside off, Hossain looks to defend it but the ball whizzes past the bat and into the keeper's gloves.

OUCH! Another bumper which goes on to hit the helmet. Shami bowls a bouncer on middle. Nayeem looks to sway away from it but cannot do so. It goes onto hit the helmet and up in the air. Kohli from the slips goes behind and takes the catch with a single hand. The Indians check up on Hasan and he is seen sharing a smile with his partner suggesting that he is fine. Physio called in to check up on him. Let's see whether he will continue or not.
Another short ball but this time down the leg side, Nayeem looks to pull at the last moment but ball goes past him and into the mitts of the keeper.
FOUR! Nicely played that! Short ball outside off, Hasan rocks on his back foot and plays the upper cut over the second slip fielder to get off the mark with a boundary.

EXCELLENT TAKE FROM SAHA AGAIN! This is a beautiful piece of bowling from Shami! Good length ball on off swinging in. Nayeem looks to defend it but the ball cuts him in half. The ball flies to the right of Saha who does very well to catch it while diving.
OUCH! This time hits the gloves. Shami bowls another short delivery opn middle, Nayeem looks to fend it off the back foot but the ball hits the gloves and goes onto the pitch.
FOUR! Beautifully played! Shami goes full outside off, Nayeem creams the drive through cover for the second boundary of the over.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off, Hossain attempts the drive but the ball passes the outside edge of his bat and Saha collects it behind the stumps.
BEATEN! Another full delivery outside off, Ebadot looks to drive yet again but fails to make any connection to it.

Fullish delivery outside off, Ebadot guides it to point where Jadeja misfields allowing the batsmen to take a single. They crossed over for a couple but umpire Erasmus has found Hossain one short. So only a single given.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Ebadot looks to drive but misses it altogether.

OUT! TIMBER! After bowling some balls outside off, Ishant goes full and hits the stumps. Briliant bowling this! Full delivery on off, Hossain looks to defend while he moves to the leg side but fails to make any connection to it. The ball whizzes past the bat and goes onto hitting the stumps. The visitors crumbel further.
Full delivery on off, Mehidy defends it to point.
Full delivery down the leg side, Nayeem looks to flick it but misses it completely.

BEATEN! Beautiful bowling but an even better take from Saha! Good length ball on off moving in. Nayeem looks to defend it but the ball smeaks through. Saha dives full length to his right and pouches it safely. Excellent stuff from Wriddhiman.
BOUNCER! Shami goes for another bumper on middle, Nayeem ducks under it.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off, Nayeem looks to guide it to third man but fails to put any bat to it.
On a length outside off, Nayeem guides it to point for nothing.
OHH! Another short ball on leg stump! Nayeem tries to fend at it but it hits him on the body.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Fullish delivery around off, Mehidy prods forward and guides this towards the backward point region for his first boundary.
Good length ball on off, Mehidy defends it towards cover.
Short ball on off, Mehidy rocks on his back foot and defends it onto the pitch.
Back of a length ball outside off, Mehidy shoulders arms to it.
FOUR! Lovely shot! This man is showing that he can bat. Full delivery outside off, Mehidy lunges forward and thrashes the ball through covers and into the fence.
Fullish ball on off, Mehidy is solid in defense. A better over for Bangladesh as 8 runs have come off it.
Good length ball on off, Nayeem pushes it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on middle, Nayeem plays it back to Shami.
FOUR! Nicely played! Shami bowls a length ball on off, Nayeem on his back foot guides it over the slip cordon and into the third man fence.
FOUR! Nicely played! Back of a length delivery outside off, Nayeem camps on his back foot and punches it to deep point for a boundary.
Short ball outside off, Nayeem attempts to play the upper cut but misses it altogether.
Good length ball on off, Nayeem defends it to cover off the back foot.
Good length ball on off, MH defends it off the front foot to the off side.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Mehidy defends it to mid on.
BEATEN! A wild slash this one though. Shorter delivery outside off, Mehidy attempts the cut shot but fails to make any connection to it.
Full delivery on off, Mehidy pushes it to cover for nothing.
PLAY AND A MISS! Ishant dishes out a full delivery outside off, Mehidy attempts the drive but misses it altogether yet again.

OUT! CAUGHT! The concussion substitute has to go. Full delivery on middle, Mehidy flicks this uppishly but he finds Pujara at short mid-wicket. He dives forward and takes the catch just inches above the ground. The square leg umpire has told Mehidy Hasan to wait in order to check whether it was a clean catch which it is and Mehidy has to go. Bangladesh have not even reached 100 and they are just two wickets away from getting bowled out.
BEATEN! Good length ball with some late swing outside off, Nayeem looks to guide this to third man but fails to put any bat on it.

FOUR LEG BYES! Full delivery down the leg side, Hasan looks to flick it but it brushes his thigh pad and goes to the fine leg fence. The replays roll in and it shows that it should have been given as byes as there was nothing on it. 100 up for the visitors.

FALLS SHORT! Short ball outside off, Nayeem looks to play the upper cut but it goes off the upper half of his bat towards third man. Jadeja runs in to take the catch but the ball falls short. It hits his hand and the ball goes towards the fence. Jadeja recovers and cleans it up. The batters take a single. If Jadeja can't catch that one, then I doubt that anyone can.
The batsman has played it to the point region.
BOUNCER! A good one at that! It is bowled on middle, Hossain ducks under it.
PLAY AND A MISS! Good length ball outside off, Hossain looks to play the drive but is beaten.  Another good over from Shami comes to an end.
Pacy inswinger pitching on middle and leg. Nayeem looks to defend but gets hit on the pads.
Full on middle and off, Nayeem defends it to the on side.
Bouncer! It is very close to the body. Nayeem takes his eyes off the ball and keeps his bat hanging with his bottom hand off the bat. It hits him on the handle of his bat.
Fuller ball on off, Nayeem looks to play it on the off side but it goes off the outer half of his bat through covers. Umesh cleans it up. Two taken.

OUT! Bowled! 5-fer for Ishant Sharma. His 10th in Tests. A proper outswinger this. Ishant uses the width of the crease and bowls it on middle. It shapes away from the batter. Nayeem looks to defend it away from his body. He misses and the off stump goes for a toss. Second 5-fer at home for Ishant. 12 years after his first.
Length ball on off, Abu does well to get bat on ball.
Short ball on middle, Al-Amin looks to pull it but the ball goes off the top edge towards cover. The batters cross over for a single.
Full delivery on middle and leg, Jayed looks to flick it but it goes off the inside edge onto the pads. No run.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pujara saves Rohit from another embarrasment of dropping a catch. Sharma had dropped a sitter in the first Test match and he was on the verge of dropping another but it was not to be as Pujara saved him. Good length ball outside off, Jayed looks to guide it to third man but the ball goes off his outside edge towards Rohit Sharma at second slip. He makes a mess of it and has no idea where the ball has gone. Luckily for him, the ball lands straight into the hands of Pujara at first slip. With this, Bangladesh have been BOWLED OUT FOR JUST 106.

FOUR! India are off the mark in style. Mayank does not wait for long. Good length ball outside off, Mayank is to quick pounce on it and he slashes it through point for a boundary. The form that this man is in, he will not miss out on those.
Hint of inward movment for Al-Amin. It is on the pads, Agarwal looks to flick but it goes off his pad to the leg side. They take a leg bye.
Length ball outside off, Rohit plays it to point.
Fuller on middle, Rohit defends it to the on side.

SIX! Rohit waits for a bit but he too gets off the mark in style. He loves playing here in Eden Gardens and he is off the mark with one of his favorite shots. Back of a length ball on middle, Rohit gets on his back foot and pulls it over backward square leg. The ball hits the cushion on the up and after a few checks the umpire raises both his hands to signal it as a maximum.
On the stumps, Rohit blocks it to get through the over. India off to a flier. 11 off the first.
Good length ball outside off, Mayank leaves it alone.
Good fielding! Full and swinging away. Mayank drives it with the swing to the left of cover. Mahmudullah there dives and saves runs for his side.
Very full outside off, Mayank squeezes it through cover-point and gets a couple.
Length ball outside off, this moves away. Mayank looks to defend but the ball goes past the inside edge.
Length delivery outside off, Mayank leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Mayank lunges forward and leaves it alone.
On the pads, Rohit glances it to the on side and gets a single.
FOUR! Just plays it with timing and not power. Length ball outside off, Mayank just guides it behind square on the off side for a boundary.
Back of a length on off, Agarwal defends it off his back foot.
On off, Agarwal keeps it out.
On the fourth stump line, Mayank does not disturb this.
Full on off and middle, Mayank gets on his front foot and defends it with authority.
Length ball outside off, Rohit just strokes it with a slant bat through point and gets a three as Taijul gives it a very good chase and cleans it up before the ropes with a slide.
Fuller on off, Agarwal defends it off the front foot.
Very full on off, Mayank defends it towards mid off.
Full around off, Mayank gets on his back foot and plays it under his eyes towards point.
On top of middle, Agarwal defends it to mid on.
FOUR! Poor ball to end the over. It is overpitched on the pads, Mayank says thank you very much and flicks it with ease through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Ohh! Full on off, this one nips back in. Rohit looks to defend but it goes off his inside edge behind square on the leg side. They take a single.
Length ball, swinging away. It is well outside off, Mayank has a slash at it but misses.
Good length ball on off, Agarwal defends it off his back foot.

OUT! Caught! Stunned silence here at Eden Gardens. Mayank has thrown it away here. Good length ball outside off, Agarwal goes chasing after it and looks to guide it wide of gully. He is unable to do so and ends up playing it uppishly to the man there. Mehidy Hasan there shows sharp reflexes as the pink ball is not easy to catch. He takes a good, sharp catch. Something to cheer about for Bangladesh. Mayank practices that shot as he walks back but it is too late, young man.
Fuller outside off, Pujara starts his innings with a calm leave.
Hits the deck hard on  off, Pujara gets the feel of the ball on his bat as he defends it off his back foot.
Full on off, Rohit pushes it to mid on.
Full outside off, Rohit leaves it alone.
Outside off, Rohit shoulders arms to it.
On the pads, Rohit tucks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball on off, Sharma plays it to point.
Punched off the back foot by the batsman.
On the pads, Pujara glances it to the on side for one.
Length ball on off, RS plays it to point.
Good length ball outside off, Rohit looks to defend but gets squared up.
The batsman has punched the ball off the back foot.
Short ball outside off, Sharma punches this to the on side and takes a single.
On a length outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to this one.
Fullish delivery outside off, Sharma flexes his arms and lets the ball go to the keeper.
Another full delivery outside off, Rohit pushes it to cover for nothing.
Back of a length delivery on off, Sharma camps on his back foot and defends it out.
Fullish delivery on middle, Sharma plays it back to the bowler.
Full ball outside off, Sharma moves a bit forward and pushes it to the cover fielder.
Strays down the leg side does Jayed. Sharma looks to flick it but misses.
Good length ball on off, Pujara defends it off the back foot to the leg side.
On a length on off, Cheteshwar is solid in defense.
Full delivery on off, Pujara pushes this back Al-Amin Hossain.
Full delivery way outside off, Pujara will play at those and lets it through to the keeper.
Back of a length delivery, Pujara rocks back and blocks it to cover.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Cheteshwar flicks it but finds the mid-wicket fielder.
Full delivery outside off, Rohit looks to push at it but it goes off the outside half. It goes uppishly towards the point fielder who collects it on the bounce.
Good length ball on off, Rohit attempts to defend it but it goes off the inside edge onto the pads. No harm done though.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off inviting Sharma for the drive. He obliges and looks to drive it but ball goes through to the keeper.
Back of a length delivery on off, Rohit works it to mid-wicket off the back foot.
BEATEN! Full delivery outside off, Rohit lunges forward to defend but the ball whizzes past the bat and into the keeper's gloves.
Another full delivery outside off, Sharma takes a few strides forward and sees the ball is way out of his range. Lets the ball go to the keeper. Only 3 runs have come from the last 6 overs.
BEATEN! Good length ball outside off swinging away a bit, Pujara attempts to defend it off the back foot but misses it.
Fullish ball in the channel outside off, Pujara lets it go to the keeper.
On middle, pushed to mid off.
Good length ball on off, Pujara defends it to cover.
FOUR! Nicely played! Good length ball from Al-Amin Hossain, Pujara stands tall and guides it past the diving gully fielder to third man for his first boundary.
On a length on off, Pujara pushes it to mid off. 4 runs have come off the over.

DROPPED! What has Al-Amin Hossain done here? If history remembers, you cannot drop Rohit Sharma. Remember his 264 in an ODI against Sri Lanka, he was dropped on 4 and then went on to play a innings which is yet to be broken. Short of a length delivery on middle, Rohit plays his favourite shot and times it well. Al-Amin is stationed at deep square leg for that very reason. He settles under it and makes a complete hash of it. Will this come back to haunt them?
Full delivery outside off, Pujara lets the ball through to the keeper.
On a length outside off, Cheteshwar does not fiddle with it and lets the ball go to the keeper.
Fullish delivery on off, Pujara pushes it to cover.
BEATEN! Beautiful bowling from Abu Jayed! Dishes a full ball outside off which moves a little bit away, Pujara looks to drive it but misses it altogether.
Another full delivery outside off, Pujara plays a nice cover drive through covers for a couple. The fielder runs after it from cover and cleans it up. TEA ON DAY 1.
Ebadot starts with a length ball outside off. Rohit does not tease that one and leaves it alone.
Good fielding! Very full outside off, Rohit stretches and looks to play it wide of gully. Mehidy Hasan at gully stretches and jumps to his right and saves a certain boundary.
FOUR! Rohit's first runs off the session. On the pads, Rohit flicks it with no fuss through mid-wicket for a boundary.

FOUR! Off the edge this time. Good length ball around off, Rohit looks to defend but the ball zips away a bit. He then looks to pull out his bat. The ball takes the outside edge and goes on the bounce wide of second slip for a boundary.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call it is. India don't lose their review but they lose their man. Length ball outside off, Rohit Sharma looks to leave it but the ball comes back in. It hits him on the pads. The Bangladesh players put in a huge appeal. The umpire agrees with them and raises his finger. Rohit has a word with his partner and then signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and the Ball Tracker shows that the ball was going to clip the top of off. Umpire's call on height.
EDGED AND FOUR! Kohli gets off the mark in a streaky way. Good length ball around off, Kohli looks to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and goes wide of gully for a boundary.
FOUR! Poor bowling this from Abu Jayed! Strays on the pads, Pujara loves it there and he just flicks it through square leg for a boundary. 50 up for India.
Full delivery on middle, Pujara works it to mid-wicket.
On a length outside off, Cheteshwar shoulders arms to this one.

FOUR! Brilliant just brilliant from Cheteshwar Pujara! Short of a length ball outside off, Pujara stands tall and thrashes it to backward point for a boundary. 15000 first class runs for Cheteshwar Pujara.
Full delivery on middle, Pujara works it to mid-wicket and takes a single.
Very full delivery on middle, Kohli defends it out to mid off.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to this one.
Back of a length ball on middle, Pujara solidly defends it back to the bowler.
BOUNCER! A good one at that! Bowls it on middle, Pujara does well to sway away from it.
Good length ball around off coming in sharply, Cheteshwar blocks it off the back foot to the off side.
Full delivery outside off, Pujara lets the ball go to the keeper.
On a length outside off, Pujara does not fiddle with it and lets it go to the keeper.
Fuller on off and middle, Kohli defends it to the on side.

FOUR! And Kolkata witnesses one of the most gorgeous looking cricketing shots. A Virat Kohli cover drive. Fuller on off, Kohli gets on his front foot, keeps a good balance and creams his drive through covers for a boundary.
On the pads, Kohli glances it wide of mid on for one.
Full on off, Pujara defends it off the front foot.
FOUR! Another delivery drifting on the pads, Pujara easily clips it away through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Full on off, Pujara defends it to get through the over.
Length ball outside off, Kohli gets on the front foot and leaves it alone.
Full on the pads, Kohli flicks it to the right of fine leg and cleans it up. Two taken.
On the fourth stump line, Virat leaves it alone.
FOUR! Gorgeous! You can run out of superlatives but Kohli's drive will still please you all the time. Full on off, Kohli lunges forward and drives it with class through covers for a boundary.
Misfield. Fuller on off, Kohli looks to play it on the on side but it goes to point off the outer half of his bat. The fielder there misfields allowing them to take a single.
Good length ball on off, Pujara looks to defend but does so off the inner half of his bat as the ball jags back in.

FOUR! Lucky but Kohli won't mind. Good length ball closer to the off pole. Kohli initially looks to play but then decides to leave. He is a bit late though as the ball goes off the face of the bat between second slip and gully and to the fence.
Length ball on off, VK plays this to point.
Outside off, Virat leaves it alone.
Fuller on off, Kohli defends it towards point and shouts a loud no to his partner.
Away from the off pole, Kohli has no business with it.
Fuller outside off, asking Kohli to drive. Virat says not today and leaves it alone.
Good length ball on middle, Pujara works it to mid-wicket.
BOUNCER! Bowls it on the leg stump line, Pujara ducks under it.
Short ball outside off, Pujara rocks on his back foot and cuts it to point where Taijul Islam collects it on the bounce.
On a length outside off, Pujara does not play at it and leaves this alone.
FOUR! Lovely shot! Back of a length ball outside off, Pujara stands tall and punches the ball past the diving Taijul Islam and into the cover fence.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to this one.
Good length ball on middle, Virat pushes this back to Al-amin Hossain.
On a length outside off, Kohli leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Beautiful bowling from Al-Amin Hossain! Good length ball outside off with some away movement. Kohli looks to defend it off the back foot but misses it altogether.
Very full delivery outside off, Kohli plays the drive to cover. Two fielders are haring after it to clean it up but cannot stop the batters from taking three.
Outside off, left alone by Cheteshwar Pujara.
Good length ball on middle, Cheteshwar defends it out.
Full delivery on off, Kohli drives it to mid off for nothing.
Short ball down the leg side, Kohli lets the ball pass to the keeper.
Good length ball on middle, Kohli looks to work it to the leg side off the back foot but gets hit on the pads. Ebadot Hossain puts ina huge appeal for LBW but the umpire is unmoved.
Short ball on middle, Kohli pulls it to deep square leg and crosses over for a single.
Full delivery outside off, Pujara shoulders arms to this one.

FOUR! This is excellent batting! Ebadot Hossain bowls a full delivery outside off, Pujara lunges forward and creams the drive through mid off for a boundary. The fielder from mid off chases after it but fails to chase it down.
On a length ball outside off, Kohli pushes it to point.
Full delivery on off, Kohli gets on his front foot and defends it to cover.
Fullish ball around off, Kohli drives but finds the cover fielder.
Outside off, Kohli does not have anything to do with it and lets the ball go to the keeper.
Fullish delivery on middle, Kohli flicks it towards mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Kohli lets the ball go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball on middle and leg, Pujara works it towards backward square leg and collects a single.

FOUR! Kohli is in the mood! Ebadot Hossain dishes out a length ball on middle, Virat creams the straight drive back past the bowler and into the fence. Brilliant stuff. 50-run stand is up between the two. A needed stand as the hosts had lost two quick wickets and these two have now got them closer to Bangladesh's total.
Good length ball outside off, Kohli lets the ball go to the keeper.
The batsman shoulders arms to let that one through.
On a length way outside off, Kohli lets the ball go to the keeper.
Back of a length ball on off, Kohli camps on his back foot and defends it out.
Short of a length delivery on middle, Pujara works it to square leg and picks up a single.
Back of a length ball on off, Kohli defends it back to the bowler off the back foot.
Full delivery on middle, Kohli blocks it out off the front foot.
Good length ball on off, Kohli defendsa it to cover and calls Pujara for a single. Virat hesitates for a bit before taking the single and decides to take it in the end.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! You cannot let these balls go through especially if you are an experienced campaigner. This is just poor from Mahmudullah. Fullish ball outside off, Pujara leans forward and plays the drive to cover where Mahmudullah misfields and allows the ball to go into the fence.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara defends it off the front foot to cover.
Flighted ball on off, Kohli plays it to the off side and takes a single. 100 up for India.
Floated ball on middle, Pujara looks to flick it but it goes off his pads to short leg. A stifled appeal is made but nothing from the umpire.
Loopy ball on middle, Pujara comes down the track and works it to square leg for a single.
Flighted ball on middle, Kohli blocks it out.
The batsman shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Loopy ball on off, Kohli defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery outside off, Pujara looks solid and defends it to cover.
On a length on off, Pujara looks to defend it but it goes off the inside edge towards square leg. The batters manage to take a single.
Full delivery on middle, Virat pushes it back to the bowler.
Fullish in length outside off, Kohli drives it but finds the fielder at cover.
Kohli defends this good length ball on off towards point and takes a single.
Fullish delivery outside off, Pujara lets the ball through to the keeper.
Floated on off, Kohli whips it to mid-wicket.

Tossed up on off, Kohli looks to drive it on the off side but it goes off the inner half of his bat through mid on for a single. That also brings up 5000 runs for Virat Kohli in Tests as captain. Fastest to achieve this feat.
Floated on the stumps, Pujara comes down the track and defends it.
Tossed up on off, Pujji keeps it out.
Once again Pujara comes down the track and keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, Pujara comes down the track and strokes it towards cover for one.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara lets the ball go to the keeper.
Full delivery on off, Pujara lunges forward and defends it out.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Pujara rocks on his back foot and punches it to cover.
Good length ball outside off, Pujara guides this to third man and picks up a couple. Taijul Islam runs across from deep point and cleans it up. India go into the lead with this couple.
Full delivery outside off, Pujara lets the ball go to the keeper.
On a length on off, Pujara defends this off the front foot.
Floated ball outside off, Kohli defends it off the front foot to cover.
Flatter delivery on middle, Kohli punches this to long on and picks up a single.
Loopy ball on middle and leg, Pujara comes down the track and works it to mid on.
Tosses this one up outside off, Pujara puts on his dancing shoes and pushes it to cover where the fielder dives to make a good stop.
Loopy ball on middle, Pujara defends this coming down the wicket.
On off, Pujara is solid in defense.
Good length ball outside off, Kohli defends it to cover and takes a single.
Short ball outside off, Pujara stands tall and cuts it firmly off the back foot to deep point for a single.
BEATEN! Not a typical Kohli shot! Jayed goes full outside off, Kohli plays a loose drive but misses it completely.
Back of a length ball outside off, Kohli leaves it alone.
Fullish delivery on middle, Kohli defends it to mid off off the front foot.
Similar ball, Kohli punches this back to Abu Jayed.
Flatter delivery on middle, Pujara works it to short mid-wicket.
Full delivery on middle, Pujara defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up ball on off, Pujara blocks it out.
Floated ball on off, Pujara comes down and pushes it back to the bowler.
The batsman has played that off the front foot and into the ground.
Flighted ball on middle, Pujara works it to square leg and keeps strike for the next over.
On a length outside off, Pujara lets the ball through to the keeper.
Good length ball on off, Pujara defends it out to mid off.
Full delivery outside off, Pujara drives it to the cover fielder.

OHH! Fullish delivery around off, Pujara looks to defend it but it hits the outside edge. The ball goes towards Shadman Islam at second slip who makes a half stop. It rolls towards short third man and the batters pick up a single.
On a length on middle, Kohli looks to flick it but the ball goes off the inside towards square leg for a single.

Full delivery outside off, Pujara plays a lovely drive to cover where the fielder dives to make a good half stop. The ball rolls to mid off. The batters look to take the single but decide against it. The mid off fielder has a shy at the stumps but misses.
Flighted ball on middle, Kohli works it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up ball on off, Virat works it through mid on for a single.
Loopy ball on off, Pujara dances down the track and whips it towards mid-wicket for a single. before the fielder can cut it off.
Full ball on middle, Kohli defends it back to the bowler.
Floated ball outside off, Virat pushes it to cover for nothing.
Flighted ball outside off, Kohli punches it to point.
Full delivery on off, Pujara attempts to defend it but it hits the outside edge of the bat and goes to the gully fielder on the bounce.
Outside off, left alone by Cheteshwar.
Another full delivery outside off, Pujara makes another leave.
FOUR! Bang! Short ball outside off, Pujara rocks on his back foot and pulls it firmly to deep mid-wicket for a boundary. Moves to 49 with that.
On a length on middle, Pujara defends it off the back foot towards mid on.
Full delivery way outside off, Cheteshwar lets the ball through to Mithun.
Flatter delivery on middle and leg, Kohli works it to deep square leg and picks up a couple before the fielder in the deep can cut it off.
Full delivery outside off, Kohli pushes it to mid off.
Tossed up ball around off, Kohli drives it to mid on for another dot.
Flighted ball on off, Pujara defends it out off the front foot.
Loopy ball on middle, Kohli works it to square leg.
FOUR! What a way to end the over. Taijul goes full on middle, Kohli plays a lovely straight drive towards mid on and picks up another boundary.
Good length ball outside off, Che leaves it alone.
Length ball around off, Pujara keeps it out.
Bouncer! It is outside off, Pujara gets away from it.
Another bouncer! This one is closer to the body, Pujara sways away from it. Making Pujara work hard for his fifty.

Fifty for Pujara! Back-to-back in the series. This has been another fine knock from him. Good length ball outside off, Pujara nudges it towards point to get to his milestone. He raises his bat as the crowd appreciate his innings. Rahane shows bottle to Pujara from the dressing room. Both Rahane and Pujara are smiling indicating there's some story.
Bouncer. Kohli hops and defends it towards point by hoping.
Full ball outside off, Pujara comes down the track and pushes it to cover.
OHH! Floated ball outside off, Pujara pads this one away towards point. There is a huge appeal for LBW but nothing from the umpire. It was probably going outside off.
Floated ball outside off, Pujara dances down the track and defends it to point.
The batsman has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.
Loopy ball on middle, Cheteshwar puts on his dancing shoes and works it to the leg side to pick up another single.
Flatter delivery outside off, Kohli lunges forward and pushes it to cover.
Fullish in length outside off, Pujara lets the ball go to the keeper.
Back of a length delivery on the leg stump line, Pujara works it off his pads through square leg for a single.
On a length on off, Kohli solidly defends it to cover for a dot ball.
Back of a length delivery outside off, Virat guides it off the back foot to point. The gully fielder runs across and collects the ball up. No run.
Fullish delivery outside off, Kohli prods forward and drives it to cover for another single.
Jayed bowls a full delivery outside off, Pujara makes another good leave to get through the over.

Full delivery on middle, Kohli whips it towards mid-wicket. Mehidy comes across and puts in a dive to stop the ball but it goes beneath him towards deep mid-wicket allowing the batsmen to take a couple. That is poor fielding from Bangladesh. They have been average in the field and easily could have stopped  a few runs in the field if they had done a little better.
Floated ball on middle, Kohli prods forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy ball on middle, Kohli works it to long on and picks up a single.
Floated ball on middle, Pujara works it nicely through mid-wicket and picks up an easy couple.
Short ball outside off, Pujara rocks on his back foot and cuts but finds the fielder at point who collects it on the bounce.
The batsman has flicked the ball off his pads. The batsmen have run through for a single.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pujara departs yet again after scoring a fifty. It has been happening quite frequently in the recent past and it has happened yet again. On a length on off with a little extra bounce on it. Pujara looks to defend it off the back foot but it goes off the outside edge towards Shadman Islam at second slip. He makes no mistake and a good stand comes to an end. Ebadot Hossain is ecstatic and brings out the Cottrell-like salute to show his enthusiasm
Good length ball outside off, Rahane lets the ball go to the keeper.
Full delivery on off, Rahane pushes it through mid off and gets off the mark with three runs. The fielder from mid off hares after it and cleans it up.
Fullish delivery outside off, Kohli pushes it to cover for nothing.

FOUR! FIFTY! 23rd fifty for Kohli in Tests! This has been a masterful innings from the maestro. He will look to continue and get a huge one after getting a good start. Coming to the ball, it is a short delivery on off, Kohli rocks on his back foot and pulls it with disdain towards deep mid-wicket for a boundary.
Short ball on middle, Kohli looks to fend it away but hits him on the elbow. The ball rolls toward gully for nothing.
Length ball on off, Rahane defends it off his back foot.
Fuller on off, Ajinkya defends it off the front foot this time.
On off, Ajinkya defends it.
Back of a length on off, Rahane hops and defends it onto the ground.
Back of a length on off, Rahane hops and defends it onto the ground.
Good length ball on off, Rahane whips it through mid-wicket and gets a couple to get through the over.
Good length ball on off, Kohli defends it off the back foot to the off side.
On a length on middle and leg, Kohli works it to deep square leg and picks up another single.
FOUR! Poor ball but still had to be put away. Ebadot bowls a low full toss on off, Rahane prods forward and creams the drive through ccovers to pick up his first boundary.
Good length ball down the leg side, Rahane attempts to flick it but misses it.
On a length outside off keeping low, Rahane looks to drive off the back foot but it hits the bottom edge and rolls to the keeper on the bounce.
WIDE! A bouncer which is bowled way over the head of Rahane who does not fiddle with it and lets the ball go to the keeper. The umpire signals it a wide.
Short ball on middle, Rahane pulls it to deep square leg. The fielder comes across from third man and cleans it up. The batters manage to take a couple.
On off, Kohli pushes it to cover and picks up a quick single.

FOUR! Nicely played! Full delivery on middle, Rahane works it to mid on. Mushfiqur comes around and looks to stop the ball diving to his left but the ball bounces over him and goes into the long on fence. Another instance of a Bangladesh player putting in a poor effort in the field.
Fullish delivery outside off, Rahane pushes it to cover and takes a single.
Good length ball on off, Kohli blocks it out.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! What can we say about Bangladesh's fielding? They have been poor throughout this innings and another one has gone through on this occasion. Full delivery outside off, Kohli lunges forward and drives it to cover where Mahmudullah lets it go past him and into the fence. Mominul runs after it from mid off  slides to parry it back but fails to do so.
Short ball outside off, Kohli punches this off the back foot to cover.
Fuller on off, Rahane defends it off his front foot.

Good shot. Good length ball outside off, Rahane leans towards the ball and drives it through covers. The ball does not have the legs to reach to the fence. The fielder mops it up. Kohli and Rahane meanwhile come back for the third.
Length ball outside off, Kohlie shoulders arms to it.
Good length ball away from the off pole. Virat does not tease that one.
Full on off, Kohli pushes it to the man at cover.
Fuller on middle, Kohli whips it through mid-wicket and gets another three as the fielder cleans it up before the ropes.
Fullish delivery outside off, Kohli defends it off the front foot towards cover.
Al-Amin Hossain bowls it full in the channel outside off, Kohli lunges forward and pushes it to cover again.
Another full one on off, Kohli plays it back to the bowler.
On a length on off, Virat plays it onto the pitch on the off side. He wants the single but is sent back.
Full delivery on middle, Kohli whips it towards mid-wicket.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Kohli pushes it to mid on.
Good length delivery on off, Rahane defends it back to the bowler.
Full delivery on off, Rahane defends it out to mid off.
On a length on middle, Jinx defends it back to the bowler.
On middle, Rahane defends it to cover.

FOUR! Shot! This is the second last ball of the day but Rahane still has no issues in putting bad balls away. Low full toss outside off, Rahane prods forward and drives it beautifully through the covers for a boundary.
Back of a length ball on middle, Rahane defends it back to the bowler. With that, it is STUMPS ON DAY 1.
Starts with a gentle delivery in the channel outside off. A good length ball, going straight on, Kohli makes an easy leave.
Brings a length delivery into the batsman with his angle, Kohli covers the line and defends it to the on side.
Angling into the batsman around off, once again Virat is firmly behind the line in defense.
Tap and run! Kohli is off the mark for the day. A good length ball outside off, Virat pushes it with an angled bat and places it with soft hands towards point. A single is taken.
Targets the off stump with a length ball, Rahane presents a straight bat and blocks it solidly.
Lands it on a fuller length and just outside off, this time Rahane presses forward and defends it towards the cover region. A decent start for both teams.
Starts with a tossed up ball outside off, Kohli gets forward to cover his stumps and shoulders arms.
Tossed up again, this time on a fuller length around off, Kohli pushes it off his front foot to short cover.
Virat has defended it by getting right behind the line of the delivery.

FOUR! Just a gentle flick and it has gone to the fence. Taijul attempts for a flatter arm ball but doesn't  get the line and length right. The length is on the shorter side, around leg, Kohli moves back and tickles it down to fine leg for a boundary.
Hangs on the back foot to a shortish delivery again and this time works it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Fullish and close to off, Kohli strides forward and pushes it to the off side.
Good length ball in the zone outside off, it's left alone by the Indian skipper.
On and around off, a length delivery, Virat sticks on the back foot in defense.
FOUR! That's bread and butter! An over-pitched delivery around off, Kohli leans forward and across before flicking it delightfully through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Good length delivery in the channel outside off, Virat watches the line and then makes a leave.
Full and on off, Kohli prods forward and defends it with a strong bottom hand.
Gets on the back foot and punches it in the direction of the bowler.
Flighted and full on off, Rahane lunges in defense.
Flatter and on off, full and skidding in, Rahane draws forward and defends it from the inner half of his bat.
Shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Floated ball, landing full on middle, Rahane uses his wrists and works it behind square leg for a single.
Tossed up ball on middle, Kohli defends it with a straight bat towards mid on.
Back of a length delivery around off, Ajinkya moves back to use his crease and defends it to the off side.
Defended off the back foot by the batsman.

FOUR! Uppish but just wide of the bowler. Fuller in length and close to off, Rahane is on the front foot as he drives it with a straight bat. He does so slightly early and hence it goes uppishly back in the direction of the bowler. It's wide of Al-Amin though and runs down to long on for a boundary. 50-run stand comes up!
Rahane has played it to the point region. One run added to the total.
Gets on the front foot to a full ball and defends it watchfully.

FOUR! Yet another sumptuous drive from the bat of the Indian skipper. Hossain overpitches outside off, Kohli takes his front leg forward and thumps his drive through the gap at covers. Majestic to watch!
Flatter on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot.
On the pads, Rahane looks to flick but misses. The ball goes to the leg side off his pads.
Floated on off, Rahane keeps it out.
Flights one on the stumps, Rahane gets on his front foot and defends it.
Tossed up on the stumps, Rahane has no problem blocking it.
On the stumps, Jinx calmly defends it to get through the over.
On the pads, Kohli flicks it but cannot go past mid-wicket.
Fuller on off, Virat defends it with a straight bat.
Around off, Kohli pushes it towards cover for one.
Good length ball around off, Rahane lunges forward and blocks it.
Length ball around off, Rahane is in no hurry and defends it.
Another ball solidly defended by Ajinkya to get through the over. Just a run off this one.
Flighted on middle and leg, Kohli whips it to deep mid-wicket for one.
Gives this a lot of air around off, Rahane flicks it but the man at short mid-wicket fails to gather it cleanly. Mid on is there to do the clean up so it does not cost any run.
Flighted on off, Rahane gets on his front foot and drives it wide of sweeper cover for a couple.
Floated on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on the stumps, Rahane defends it calmly.
Gets behind the line of the ball and defends this onto the ground.
Good length ball on off, Kohli keeps it out.

Poor from Bangladesh. Length ball on off, Kohli nudges it towards cover-point and looks for a single. Mahmudullah moves to his left and looks to keep it down to one but he is a bit casual in his approach and the ball goes right between his legs allowing Virat to get the second.
Length ball on off, Kohli guides it towards point for one.
Around off, Rahane just places it towards cover for one.
Another easy single. Kohli just plays it towards cover for one.

FOUR! Uncontrolled but wide enough to go past the diving keeper. Short ball around the body, Rahane looks to pull but he does so off the top edge. It goes to the left of the keeper. Mithun dives on that side but the ball is well wide of him and it goes to the fine leg fence. The lead now goes past 100.
Floated on off, VK pushes it towards mid off.
Around the pads, Kohli flicks it to the leg side for a single.
Flighted on middle, Rahane strokes it to mid on.
Floated on middle, Rahane defends it towards mid on.
On the stumps, AR blocks it.
Floated on off, Rahane looks to play it on the off side but the ball goes off the outer half of his bat towards backward point for one.
Fuller on off, Rahane defends it with a straight bat.
Length ball on off, Rahane punches it to the off side and gets to the other end.
Good length ball on off, Kohli defends it solidly off his front foot.
Length ball around off, Kohli glances it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball around off, VK defends it off the front foot.
Full around off, Kohli defends it to mid off.
Floated on off, Rahane looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of his bat to the on side. They take a single.

Ohh! First ball that has turned and bounced. Taijul bowls it slower through the air around off, Kohli looks to defend but the ball spins away and squares him up. This will give confidence to all the spinners in this game.
Flighted on off, Kohli pushes it to cover.
Around the pads, Kohli glances it towards mid-wicket for one.
Another misfield, this time it is Kayes. Flighted on off, Rahane strokes it towards cover. Imrul Kayes there is lethargic in his approach and misfields allowing them to take a single.
Another spinning delivery to get through the over. Taijul gives this air around off, Kohli looks to defend but once again gets beaten by the spin.
FOUR! Not a welcome Ebadot would like. Fuller outside off, Rahane shuffles across a bit to his off stump and creams his drive through covers for a boundary.
Goes slightly shorter. Rahane defends it off his back foot.

Almost chopped on. Back of a length outside off, Rahane looks to pull but gets a big inside edge. It misses the stumps and goes to the left of the keeper. Mithun does really well diving to his left and saving a certain edgy boundary.
Fuller on off, Rahane nudges it towards point for one.
Good length ball around off, Kohli defends it with a straight bat.
Full outside off, Kohli gets on his front foot and drives it through covers. Al-Amin Hossain at sweeper cover runs to his right and shows good football skills as he saves two runs for his side.
Floated on the stumps, Ajinkya keeps it out.
FOUR! Magnificent shot! Flighted on middle, Rahane comes down the track and whips it against the spin through the cow corner region for a boundary.

Fifty for Rahane. He has once again got to his half ton. The Indian Test vice captain has been in good form lately and he is carrying it on. Floated on off, Rahane looks to defend but it goes off the inside edge to the on side to get to his fifty. He raises his bat as the crowd cheers his knock. Time to convert this into a 3-figure score now Jinxy?
On the pads, Kohli whips it through mid-wicket for a couple.
Tossed up on middle, Virat milks it through mid on for one.
Play and a miss. Tossed up around off, Rahane looks to defend but gets beaten due to the away spin.
Good length ball outside off, Kohli leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off and middle, Kohli glances it through mid-wicket. The duo of Rahane and Kohli is quick between the wickets and they manage to get three. Excellent running between the two.
Length ball on off, Rahane defends it off the front foot.
Fuller around off, Ajinkya strokes it through point for one.
Bouncer! Kohli looks to pull but misses.

FOUR BYES! Poor ball from Ebadot. Overcooks the bouncer. It is well down the leg side. Kohli looks to pull but it is wide of him. Mithun dives and stretches to his left. He gets a glove to it but had no chance stopping that. The lead now is 130.

OUT! Caught! Soft, soft dismissal for Rahane. It is a nothing delivery. Short outside off, Rahane looks to cut but ends up slicing it to the left of the man at point. Ebadot Hossain takes a simple catch. The 99-run stand is broken. Once again, just like Pujara, Rahane too does not hang around long after getting to his fifty.
Flighted on off, Jadeja drives it through covers and gets off the mark with a couple.
Excellent ball. Flighted outside off, this one spins in. Jadeja looks to defend but gets his bat back in.
Tossed up on off, Ravindra looks to defend but the ball goes behind square on the off side off the outside edge. The batsmen take three.
Good leave but that excited the visitors. Flighted outside off, Kohli gets on his front foot and leaves it alone.
Tossed up on off, Kohli pushes it straight down the ground.
Good length ball on middle and leg, Jadeja defends it off the front foot.
On off, Jaddu defends it calmly.
Length ball outside off, RJ leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Jadeja leaves it alone.
On off, Jadeja pushes it to cover.
Good length ball outside off, Jadeja shoulders arms to it.
Floated on the stumps, Kohli keeps it out.
On off, defended by Kohli.
Slightly shorter on off, Kohli cuts it to point.
Around the pads, Kohli glances it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up on off, Kohli pushes it to mid off.
On the pads, Kohli works it down to the leg side and keeps the strike.
Pitches it up and around off, Kohli gets forward and plays a punchy drive to the left of the mid off fielder.
Back of a length ball on middle, Kohli gets on top of the bounce and turns it through square leg for a single. Moves to 91!
Angling away from the batsman, on a good length, Jadeja guards his stumps and leaves it.

Appeal for an lbw, turned down! A confused Mominul first gestures about the inside edge and then about it being high. The replays show that it pitched well outside the leg stump. A length delivery at 133.7 kph, Jadeja tries flicking from the crease but misses. The appeal is made but it's unsuccessful. Reason is already mentioned above.
Fullish and on off, Jadeja drives it off the front foot to mid off.
Way wide outside off, an easy leave for Jadeja.
Brilliant! Too full in length on off, drive is out again as Kohli sends it rolling through the carpet to sweeper cover. A couple is taken.
Tossed up ball on off, Kohli presses forward and defends it to the off side.
Very full again from Taijul and it's drilled through covers for a single.
Too full and on middle, forced towards wide mid on.
Floated full ball on off, Jadeja strides forward and works it with the spin to deep mid-wicket for one.
Uses the away spin and eases his drive through covers for a single. Kohli moves to 95!
Almost nicks it behind! Good length delivery in the channel outside off, holding its line, Kohli has a push inside the line, with limited front foot movement, and gets beaten.
Extra bounce here. Ebadot hits the deck hard around off, Kohli looks to defend but it goes off the upper half of his bat towards gully on a bounce.
Back of a length, Kohli defends it off the back foot.
Fuller on off, Kohli defends it.
FOUR! Classic Kohli! Good length ball on off, Kohli gets on his front foot and drives it on the up through covers to get to 99. A trademark cover drive from the King to get one away from another ton.
Kohli is in no hurry as he leaves this ball alone.
Tossed up on off, Jadeja nudges it to the right of mid on and gives Kohli the strike. There is a huge cheer from the crowd.
Tossed up on middle, Kohli defends it off the front foot.

HUNDRED FOR KOHLI! Number 27 in Tests! The captain leading from the front. This has been a brilliant knock from the skipper. He gets into the history books by becoming the first Indian to get a century in a Day-Night Test. Floated around the pads, Virat glances it behind square on the leg side and takes a couple to get to his milestone. Virat removes his helmet and raises his bat as the crowd and his teammates rise and applaud the knock from the King! His 41st century as skipper across all formats, joint most. Equals Ricky Ponting's record. Time to convert this into another double hundred, Super V?
Flighted on off, Virat pushes it to cover.
Around off, Kohli strokes it wide of cover for one.
Flighted on middle, Jaddu eases it through mid on for a single.
Serves a length ball in the line of the stumps, Jadeja tries to flick but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Gentle delivery. On a length and wide outside off, Jadeja leaves and it dies in front of the keeper.
Back of a length delivery way wide outside off, Jadeja lets it go through to the keeper. Once again Mithun collects it on the bounce.
Fuller and on off, Jadeja drives it from the back foot but straight to mid off.

Too full in length around off, Jadeja tries to drive through the line but it catches the inner portion of the blade and hurries past the bowler. Ravindra wants a run but is sent back as the mid off fielder misses his shy at the striker's end. Ebadot had to take evasive action to avoid getting hurt as he was in line of the throw.
Chooses to leave the ball outside his off stump.
Tossed up ball outside off, defended from the back foot to the off side.
Full and flighted on off, driven with the spin to the left of the mid off fielder for a single.
Defended off the front foot by the batsman presenting the full face of the bat.
Presses forward to a full ball and works it with the spin through mid-wicket for one.
Loopy full ball outside off, Virat pushes it with the turn to sweeper cover for one.
Slower through the air and a bit on the shorter side as it lands around off. Jadeja moves back and helps it with soft hands to mid-wicket. He eyes a run but the Indian skipper ain't interested.

EDGY FOUR! A length delivery close to off, a hint of away movement there, Kohli, who stands a few steps ahead of the crease, tries to drive through covers but it catches the outside edge and runs down to third man for a boundary.
FOUR! Cracking this time! Jayed arrows in a fuller length ball on off, angling in after pitching, Kohli presses forward and across before caressing it down the ground for a boundary at long on.
FOUR! Hat-trick of boundaries! Kohli is motoring. Uses his fabulous wrists this time and flicks it beautifully past the short mid-wicket fielder for a glorious boundary.

FOUR! Kohli is on fire! He is putting on a show at Eden Gardens and the crowd is just loving it. Truly a masterclass from a masterful batsman. Full in length and outside off, Virat drives it on the up and creams it through the gap at covers. Perfect timing and placement.

Nearly the fifth boundary there. A lovely straight drive from the bat of the Indian skipper is obstructed by Jayed with his right foot. He deflects it wide of mid on as the fielder from there gives the chase. They take a couple of runs.

Width on offer outside off, Kohli just uses the pace of the bowler and glides it down to third man for a single. 19 from the over and India have zoomed their lead to 173! Expensive start to the day for Abu!
Tossed up ball around off, Kohli defends it from the back foot to the off side.
Too full in length on middle, worked through mid-wicket for a single.
Gets on the front foot to a full ball and eases it to long on for another run in this over.
Flatter and close to off, Virat remains on the back foot and blocks it solidly.
Shows the full face of the bat and defends the ball off the back foot.
Flighted and on off, Kohli stretches well forward and defends again.
Good length ball outside off, Jadeja leaves it alone.
Full on off, Jadeja pushes it to mid off.
Full on the stumps, Jadeja comes down a bit and pushes it to cover.
On the pads, Jaddu flicks it to mid-wicket.
Length ball on off, Ravindra defends it off the front foot.
Fuller on off, Jadeja keeps it out to get through the over.
Floated on off, Kohli defends it off the front foot.
Tossed up on off, Kohli whips it to mid on.
Floated on off, Kohli keeps it out.
Tossed up on off, VK defends it.
Tossed up on off, Kohli pushes it to cover.
Flights one on the stumps, Kohli defends it.
Full on off, Jadeja pushes it to mid off.
On off, Jaddu pushes it to point for one.
Short ball down the leg side, Kohli does not fiddle with it and leaves it alone.
Back of a length on off, Kohli pulls it to deep mid-wicket for one.
On the stumps, VK blocks.
Full on off, Jadeja pushes it to mid off.
FOUR! Flighted on off, Kohli gets on his front foot and drives it uppishly wide of cover. Kayes dives but does not get his hand to it and the ball races away to the fence.
Flighted on off, Kohli pushes it to cover by coming down the track.
Floated on leg, Virat glances it to the leg side for a single.
Tossed up on the stumps, Jadeja pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted on middle, Jadeja strokes it wide of mid on for a single.
Floated on off, Kohli defends it to get to Lunch on Day 2!
Length ball on off, Jadeja defends it off the front foot to cautiously start the session.

OUT! Bowled! Jadeja has completely misread that and left a ball which is coming in with the angle. Good length ball pitching just around off and it comes in with the angle. Jadeja does not pick it and leaves it alone. The ball goes on to disturb the off pole. The break seems to have brought in a lapse in concentration for Ravindra. He won't look back at it fondly and even if he tries to forget it, his teammates won't make that process any easy.
Length ball outside off, Saha watches the ball and leaves it alone.

FOUR! The local boy is off the mark in style. Full outside off, Saha gets on his front foot and drives it right off the meat of his bat through covers for a boundary. The crowd loves it and goes up in cheers.
Shows calmness and follows the boundary with a solid front foot defense.
Full on the pads, Saha flicks it through mid-wicket and comes back for the third as the fielder cleans it up before the ropes. Eventful first over of the session. 7 runs and a wicket.
Flighted on off, Saha defends it off the front foot.
Floated on middle and leg, Wriddhiman gets on his front foot and blocks it.
Bowls it fuller on middle and leg, Saha blocks it.
Tossed up on off, Saha gets on his front foot and defends it.

Ohh! Taijul bowls it slower through the air on off, it spins off the deck. Saha looks to defend but gets a thick outside edge which goes through to the third man region. They take a single as the man from backward point cleans it up.
Nicely tossed up on the stumps, Kohli defends his first ball of the session.
Good length ball around off, Wriddhiman defends it off his back foot.
Length ball outside off, no movement on this one. Saha shoulders arms to this.
Good length ball on off. Jayed goes wide of the crease and makes it come in with the angle. Saha blocks it.
Fuller around off, Saha defends it off the inner half of his bat towards mid off. Seems to have lost a bit of balance of his back foot as he looks behind as soon as he defends it.
Full on off, Saha defends it towards cover and calls no to his partner.
Full on off, Saha pushes it to cover. Maiden for Jayed.
Shorter on off, Kohli whips it to deep mid-wicket for a run. First run for Kohli in this session.
Short again around off, Saha gets on his back foot and punches it to sweeper cover for one.
Floated on off, Kohli pushes it straight down the ground.
Flighted on middle and off, Virat looks to defend but it goes to the on side off the inside edge. They take a single.

FOUR! Tossed up on off, Saha gets on his front foot and drives it through covers. The fielder there gives it a half-hearted chase and fails to stop it. Taijul is unimpressed with the effort and rightfully so. Bangladesh look jaded in the field not now but from the start of the innings.
Shorter on middle and leg, Saha watches it till the end and defends this off his back foot.

EDGED AND FOUR! Good length ball around off, it comes in a bit off the deck. Kohli looks to play it on the on side but he is a bit late in his shot and the ball goes off the leading edge towards the backward point fence for a boundary.
Length ball outside off, Kohli leaves it alone. Extra bounce on this one.

OUT! Caught! Superman catch by Taijul! He is showing his teammates how to field. In Taijul's previous over there was a lethargic effort and he was not happy and he shows why. Poor ball from Ebadot. It is full on the pads, a nothing delivery. Kohli flicks it uppishly looking to score a maximum. Tajul, who is standing ahead of the ropes at deep backward square leg, runs, stretches and dives to his right to pluck this out of thin air and takes a blinder. Kohli's brilliant innings comes to an end. He walks off with a smile as even he cannot believe what has happened. Something special was needed to get rid of King Kohli and something magical has happened.
Ashwin is off the mark. On the pads, Ashwin glances it fine down the leg side for a single.
Outside off, left alone.
On the pads, Saha flicks it to the on side. End of a good over this. 4 runs and a wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Ravichandran leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Ashwin defends it off the front foot.
Fuller on off, Aswhin defends it late off his back foot.
Full outside off, Ashwin shoulders arms to it. The ball reaches to the keeper around chest height. Good bounce on this one.
Length ball on off, Ashwin defends it off his back foot.
Ohh! Full way outside off, asking Ashwin to drive. He goes chasing after it fortunately for him he misses it completely and does not edge it.
Length ball outside off, Saha leaves it alone.
Outside off, Wriddhiman leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Saha leaves it alone.
WIDE! Way outside off, too wide. Saha leaves it alone. Wided by the umpire.

NOT OUT! Waste of a review! It looked like there was nothing and there was indeed nothing. Good length ball outside off, it comes in. Saha leaves it alone. The ball goes closely off his glove and bat as he tries to take his bat up. There is a stifled appeal. Ebadot is confident and he convinces his skipper to take it upstairs. Mominul signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and shows no spike on the Ultra Edge. Bangladesh lose one of their two reviews.
On middle, Saha strokes it to mid on.
Length ball outside off, Saha leaves it alone.
Length ball on off, Ashwin defends it.
Around the pads, RA flicks it to the on side.
Length ball outside off, it is moving away. Ashwin leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Ashwin punches it to cover.
Length ball outside off, Ashwin leaves it alone.
Full on the pads, Ashwin flicks it to fine leg and keeps the strike.
FOUR BYES! Short ball down the leg side. Ashwin looks to pull but misses. Mithun dives to his left but fails to stop it and the ball goes to the fence.

FOUR! Poor fielding from Abu Jayed. Full and jagging back in Ashwin flicks it through square leg. Abu Jayed comes running in and looks to stop it with a dive but he cannot do it cleanly. The ball deflects off his body and into the fence.
FOUR! Pulled away with disdain. Back of a length ball on off, Ashwin gets on his back foot and pulls it over mid-wicket for a boundary.
Length ball on off, Ashwin looks to defend it with soft hands but gets a thick outside edge which goes to the man at gully on a bounce.
WIDE! Wild delivery outside off. Ashwin leaves it alone as the ball is well over the tramline.

FOUR BYES! Another wild delivery this time down the leg side. Ashwin looks to pull but misses. Mithun dives but has absolutely no chance of saving that. It goes to the fence. Four byes signalled. Ebadot is a lucky man as it has not been wided.
Now delivers a ball close to the stumps after two wild deliveries. Ashwin defends it off the front foot.
Length delivery on middle, this one is the one that has actually swung. Saha does well to defend it.
Full on off,  Saha keeps it out.
Bangladesh struggling to control the new pink ball under lights. Fuller down the leg side. Saha looks to flick but misses.
Length ball on middle, Saha flicks it to the on side for a single.
Good length ball on off, it jags back in. Wriddhiman Saha defends it off the front foot.

OUT! Umpire's call. The impact is marginally umpire's call. Good length ball pitching outside off, Ashwin looks to flick but misses. The ball hits his pad and there is a huge appeal from the Bangladesh bowlers. Umpire Joel Wilson raises his finger after a few thoughts. Ashwin has a word with Saha and then signals the 'T'. Replay rolls in and it shows the impact is just about umpire's call. India don't lose their review but Ashwin has to walk back.
On the pads, Saha flicks it to the on side for a single.
Fuller on middle, Umesh pushes it to mid on.
